<br>
I hate rules .. the less the better. Rules often create arguments. But, then again, there's the confusion without them, and sometimes they prevent arguments.<br>
<br>
Anyway... <br>
<br>
1. Time was, we had a raid officer. I looked over the roster.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.guildmagic.com/guild_characters.cfm?ID=11286" target="top">Guild Roster</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
I can't tell. Do we have one? I know Dlite's keeping track of epics, but I probably missed a message or something if she assumed Iume's role as raid officer. <br>
<br>
2. Is Tuesday still reserved for Horizons guildee epics? In other words, wouldn't it be inappropriate if I told everyone I want to raid The Hole for King Rat on Tuesday, March 4, because I want the Idol of the Underking? <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:helvetica;font-size:xx-small;">(I suppose an exception would be if no epic raid was materializing for the 4th and it was an otherwise available night.)</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
3. Is there a priority to classes in epic raiding on Tuesdays? Aren't clerics, shamans and enchanters ahead of others because of the importance of their epics to guild raids?<br>
<br>
4. When we do an epic raid, let's say there are two frogloks that need an epic piece that drops? Do they roll for it? Or, is the froglok that's farther along in her epic get the piece.<br>
<br>
5. Finally, whose call is it to decide what we do on Tuesdays? I know we're encouraged to take initiative and schedule raids on our own. But Tuesdays? Is this a bit different? Is this for an officer to decide?<br>
<br>
